%text
Let the equation of the plane be $ax+by+cz+d=0$. Since this plane is perpendicular to $x+2y+3z=5$ and $3x+3y+z=0$ therefore,
%
\begin{align}
  a+2b+3c=3a+3b+c=0
\end{align}

%text
Let the equation of the plane be $ax+by+cz+d=0$. Since this plane is perpendicular to $x+2y+3z=5$ and $3x+3y+z=0$ therefore,
%
\begin{align}
  a+2b+3c=3a+3b+c=-1
\end{align}
